subtasks.details:
Add routes to public/index.php after existing Xtream API routes:

// Stream proxy routes (no middleware - auth handled in controller)
$app->get('/live/{username}/{password}/{stream_id}.{ext}', [StreamProxyController::class, 'proxyLiveStream']);
$app->get('/movie/{username}/{password}/{stream_id}.{ext}', [StreamProxyController::class, 'proxyVodStream']);
$app->get('/series/{username}/{password}/{stream_id}.{ext}', [StreamProxyController::class, 'proxySeriesStream']);

Route parameters:
- {username}: Client username (string)
- {password}: Client password (string)
- {stream_id}: Stream identifier (numeric)
- {ext}: File extension (m3u8, ts, mp4, mkv, avi, flv, etc.)

NOTE: Do NOT add ClientAuthMiddleware to these routes - authentication is handled inside controller methods using path parameters instead of query parameters.

Import StreamProxyController at top of file:
use App\Controllers\StreamProxyController;
